---
description: Parallel delegation guardrails
alwaysApply: true
---

For non-trivial tasks, parallel specialist delegation is preferred when it reduces cycle time without harming quality.

## Required guardrails

1. Parallelize only independent specialties with non-overlapping write ownership in the same batch.
2. Prefer review/findings phases in parallel; converge to a single implementation writer by default.
3. Resolve security-sensitive recommendation conflicts before implementation proceeds.
4. Do not exceed the declared budget envelope (token/cost/time) without explicit rationale in closeout.
5. If unresolved high-severity conflict remains after synthesis, halt and report instead of forcing implementation.
